    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-beef-peposo-with-saffron-butter-orzo-with-dessert/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced</strong> <strong>beef </strong>to the dish with your <strong>cracked black pepper</strong> and cook for 2 min or until lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-beef-peposo-with-saffron-butter-orzo-with-dessert/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your<strong> leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-beef-peposo-with-saffron-butter-orzo-with-dessert/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once lightly browned, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and give it a good mix up</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced leek</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-beef-peposo-with-saffron-butter-orzo-with-dessert/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>red wine paste</strong> and<strong> tomato paste</strong> with your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[550ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>bay leaf[ves] </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for 45-50 min or until the sauce is rich and the beef is tender \u2013 this is your<strong> baked Tuscan-style beef peposo</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-beef-peposo-with-saffron-butter-orzo-with-dessert/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the beef has had 35 min, reboil a kettle</p><p>Combine your <strong>orzo </strong>and <strong>saffron</strong> in an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and give it a good mix up</p><p>Cover tightly with<strong> tin foil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 15-18 min or until the orzo is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>cooked orzo</strong></p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-beef-peposo-with-saffron-butter-orzo-with-dessert/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the beef is ready, season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and set aside, with the lid on, for 3-4 min for the flavours to develop</p><p>Once the orzo is cooked, add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>saffron butter orzo</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-beef-peposo-with-saffron-butter-orzo-with-dessert/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> baked Tuscan-style beef peposo </strong>over the<strong> saffron butter orzo</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
